parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can cause accidents or near-misses, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intentions to stop or slow down.
symptoms: The brake lights do not illuminate
the socket and plastic on the bulb are melted
and the brake lights may work intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The condensation in the headlights can reduce visibility at night, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Water or fog accumulates inside the headlight assembly
reducing the effectiveness of the headlights
and potentially causing the bulb to explode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signals and hazard lights can cause accidents or near-misses, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intentions to turn or change lanes.
symptoms: The turn signals and hazard lights do not illuminate
the hazard switch clicks or makes a noise
and the turn signal relay/switch may malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of problems, including brake light failure, turn signal failure, and potentially even electrical fires.
symptoms: causing problems with the brake lights

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety hazards, including fires, loss of critical vehicle functions, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The dashboard lights illuminate and go out
the horn does not produce a sound
the speedometer sticks or fails to work
the climate control switch stays on one setting
and the vehicle catches on fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument panel cluster can cause the speedometer to stick or fail to work, leading to accidents or traffic violations.
symptoms: The speedometer sticks or fails to work
and the speedometer fails to reset to 0 mph.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the turn signals can cause accidents or increase the risk of accidents due to lack of visibility.
symptoms: the turn signals fail to work
and the turn signal wiring shorts out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause accidents or increase the risk of accidents due to loss of braking ability.
symptoms: The brake pedal must be pressed all the way to the floor
and the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the anti-theft system can cause the vehicle to fail to start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety hazards.
symptoms: the theft system light on the dashboard pops on and off
and the vehicle locks and unlocks doors when the turn signal is used.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold gasket can cause the engine to overheat, leading to costly repairs, engine damage, and potential safety risks, such as loss of power while driving.
The failure of the engine head gasket can cause the engine to overheat, leading to costly repairs, engine damage, and potential safety risks, such as loss of power while driving.
The failure of the rocker arm post can cause the engine to stall, leading to potential safety risks, such as loss of power while driving.
The corrosion of the engine support bracket can cause the radiator to fall, leading to potential safety risks, such as loss of coolant, overheating, and engine damage.
The engine stalling can cause loss of power, leading to potential safety risks, such as accidents or loss of control.
